{#- 404 illustration — nine of the twelve EU flag stars in their
    canonical circular positions, with three at the top (11, 12, 1
    o'clock) caught and carried away by a left-to-right wind. The
    fragments form a single sweeping trail rather than three static
    clusters: anchor remnants at each original position, then a long
    arc of shards drifting rightward and gently rising as they go.
    A faint outline of the European landmass sits behind. Metaphor:
    a piece of the Union has gone missing — and the wind is taking it.

    Coordinate notes
    ----------------
    viewBox is 600 × 480 (small, fits in a card-sized container). The
    nine remaining stars sit on an invisible circle centred at
    (300, 250) with radius 130; star outer radius 24 keeps the EU
    flag readable without overlap. The 11, 12, and 1 o'clock slots
    are empty; three anchor shards mark the originals and eight more
    sweep left → right in a wind trail with decreasing size and
    opacity, increasing rotation, ending near the right edge.

    Styling is applied via SVG presentation attributes (fill /
    opacity) rather than external CSS so the illustration renders
    correctly even if the stylesheet hasn't loaded or has been
    cached stale. Theme tinting still uses `currentColor` for the
    Europe outline so the body text colour drives its tint.

    Renders pure SVG (no Nunjucks vars) so it inlines verbatim. -#}
<svg viewBox="0 0 600 480"
     width="100%"
     class="notfound-illustration"
     role="img"
     aria-labelledby="notfound-illustration-title notfound-illustration-desc"
     preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet"
     aria-hidden="true"
     focusable="false">
  <title id="notfound-illustration-title">A piece of the Union has gone missing</title>
  <desc id="notfound-illustration-desc">Nine of the twelve European Union flag stars are arranged in their canonical circle. The three stars at the top of the circle have broken into golden fragments, swept rightward by an implied wind in a long trail that fades into the upper-right edge. A faint outline of the European landmass sits behind.</desc>

  <defs>
    {#- 5-pointed star polygons. Outer radius noted in each id; inner
        radius is outer × 0.382 (golden-ratio inverse) for a regular
        star. Origin centred so the symbol can be placed by translate
        on the use element. -#}
    <symbol id="notfound-star-r24" overflow="visible">
      <polygon points="0,-24 5.39,-7.42 22.82,-7.42 8.72,2.83 14.11,19.42 0,9.17 -14.11,19.42 -8.72,2.83 -22.82,-7.42 -5.39,-7.42"/>
    </symbol>
    <symbol id="notfound-shard-r12" overflow="visible">
      <polygon points="0,-12 2.69,-3.71 11.41,-3.71 4.36,1.41 7.06,9.71 0,4.59 -7.06,9.71 -4.36,1.41 -11.41,-3.71 -2.69,-3.71"/>
    </symbol>
    <symbol id="notfound-shard-r8" overflow="visible">
      <polygon points="0,-8 1.79,-2.47 7.61,-2.47 2.91,0.94 4.70,6.47 0,3.06 -4.70,6.47 -2.91,0.94 -7.61,-2.47 -1.79,-2.47"/>
    </symbol>
    <symbol id="notfound-shard-r5" overflow="visible">
      <polygon points="0,-5 1.12,-1.55 4.76,-1.55 1.82,0.59 2.94,4.05 0,1.91 -2.94,4.05 -1.82,0.59 -4.76,-1.55 -1.12,-1.55"/>
    </symbol>
  </defs>

  {#- Faint Europe landmass. The europe-outline partial projects into
      a 1000 × 700 viewBox; we shrink it to ~ 540 × 480 area inside
      our 600 × 480 viewBox via translate + scale, centred behind the
      star ring. `opacity` is set as an SVG attribute (not CSS) so
      stale stylesheets can't leave the silhouette fully opaque.
      `fill="currentColor"` lets the body text colour tint it. -#}
  <g class="notfound-illustration-europe"
     aria-hidden="true"
     fill="currentColor"
     opacity="0.08"
     transform="translate(30 50) scale(0.54 0.54)">
    {%- include "europe-outline.njk" %}
  </g>

  {#- 9 EU flag stars in canonical positions (11, 12, 1 o'clock empty).
      Circle: centre (300, 250), radius 130. Fill set as SVG attribute
      so the illustration renders even with no CSS loaded. -#}
  <g class="notfound-illustration-stars"
     aria-hidden="true"
     fill="#f5b800">
    <use href="#notfound-star-r24" transform="translate(430 250)"/>   {#- 3 o'clock -#}
    <use href="#notfound-star-r24" transform="translate(412.6 315)"/> {#- 4 o'clock -#}
    <use href="#notfound-star-r24" transform="translate(365 362.6)"/> {#- 5 o'clock -#}
    <use href="#notfound-star-r24" transform="translate(300 380)"/>   {#- 6 o'clock -#}
    <use href="#notfound-star-r24" transform="translate(235 362.6)"/> {#- 7 o'clock -#}
    <use href="#notfound-star-r24" transform="translate(187.4 315)"/> {#- 8 o'clock -#}
    <use href="#notfound-star-r24" transform="translate(170 250)"/>   {#- 9 o'clock -#}
    <use href="#notfound-star-r24" transform="translate(187.4 185)"/> {#- 10 o'clock -#}
    <use href="#notfound-star-r24" transform="translate(412.6 185)"/> {#- 2 o'clock -#}
  </g>

  {#- Wind-blown shard trail. Reads as the three missing stars (11, 12,
      1 o'clock) caught and carried by a left-to-right wind. Anchored
      shards near each original star position show the breakup; the
      trail sweeps rightward and arcs slightly upward as shards drift
      further from where the stars stood. Sizes step down from r12 →
      r8 → r5, opacities step down from 0.88 → 0.15, and rotations
      tilt progressively clockwise (more spin further into the wind)
      so the trail reads as motion rather than a static scatter.

      Anchor coordinates: 11 o'clock ≈ (235, 137), 12 o'clock = (300,
      120), 1 o'clock ≈ (365, 137). Trail x-range: 215 → 525; trail
      y-range: 130 → 50 (rising ~80 px over 310 px of horizontal
      travel — the arc of a gentle wind lift). -#}
  <g class="notfound-illustration-fragments"
     aria-hidden="true"
     fill="#f5b800">
    {#- Three small anchor shards at each original star position, showing
        where the wind first caught the stars. Low opacity so they read
        as fading remnants rather than fresh debris. -#}
    <use href="#notfound-shard-r5"  transform="translate(232 135) rotate(-12)" opacity="0.42"/>
    <use href="#notfound-shard-r5"  transform="translate(298 118) rotate(6)"   opacity="0.46"/>
    <use href="#notfound-shard-r5"  transform="translate(363 134) rotate(20)"  opacity="0.42"/>

    {#- Wind trail — eight shards sweeping left to right, arcing up. -#}
    <use href="#notfound-shard-r12" transform="translate(215 128) rotate(-5)"  opacity="0.88"/>
    <use href="#notfound-shard-r12" transform="translate(260 112) rotate(12)"  opacity="0.78"/>
    <use href="#notfound-shard-r8"  transform="translate(305 96)  rotate(24)"  opacity="0.68"/>
    <use href="#notfound-shard-r8"  transform="translate(350 82)  rotate(34)"  opacity="0.56"/>
    <use href="#notfound-shard-r8"  transform="translate(395 72)  rotate(42)"  opacity="0.46"/>
    <use href="#notfound-shard-r5"  transform="translate(440 64)  rotate(52)"  opacity="0.36"/>
    <use href="#notfound-shard-r5"  transform="translate(485 56)  rotate(62)"  opacity="0.25"/>
    <use href="#notfound-shard-r5"  transform="translate(525 50)  rotate(72)"  opacity="0.15"/>
  </g>
</svg>
